Hublot was live with @andreas_caminada_schauenstein and @ricardoguadalupe, for a unique cooking session from @schloss_schauenstein. Aiming to constantly create culinary surprises, the three-star chef presented his famous “Onion Physalis”- a delight for the eyes and the palate. Reproduce this delicious dish at home, following the recipe.
 
 
ONION PHYSALIS
 
RED ONION CEVICHE
3 red onions (500g)
7 limes (245g juice)
2 celery stalks
5g ginger
15g coriander seeds
250g water
Peel and chop onion and ginger. Also chop the celery stalks and then blend everything. Put the coriander on top and let it steep for 2 days. Strain the mixture, season with lauter sugar, bind with xanthan water and season again with salt.
 
PICKLED RED ONION (10 pieces)
65g sugar
200ml table vinegar
600ml beet juice
22.5g salt
1 sprig tarragon
10g mustard seeds
Boil pickling stock, pour on peeled onion in jars and steam for 20min.
 
PICKLED JALAPENOS (10 pieces)
65g sugar
200ml table vinegar
600ml water
22.5g salt
1 sprig tarragon
10g mustard seeds
Boil pickling stock, pour on jalapeños in jars and steam for 20min.
 
PICKLED PHYSALIS
250g physalis
140ml rice vinegar
200ml water
65g mirin
60g honey
35g sugar
6.2g salt
Boil pickling stock and pour hot over physalis.
 
WHITE AND RED SALTED ONION
Cook one onion each whole on sea salt. 180°C for about 15min. Peel, cut into segments.
GREEN TOMATOES PICKLED (10 pieces/65g)
65g sugar
200ml table vinegar
600ml water
22.5g salt
1 sprig tarragon
10g mustard seeds
Boil pickling stock, put on peeled onion in jars and steam for 20min.
 
CHILI OIL
20g chili flakes
200g oil
Vacuum the chili flakes with the oil for 48h at 55°C.
 
HERBS OIL
2 bunches of chives
400g oil
Blend the chives with the oil in the Thermomix for 8 minutes at 80°C, then cool on ice.

PIKE PERCH 
2 pieces of pike-perch fillet (boned and without skin)
salt
rapeseed oil
dill flowers for garnishing
Season the pike-perch on both sides with salt and rub with rapeseed oil. Place on a baking tray, cover directly with cling film and cook at 55°C for about 8 minutes with steam, alternatively with top and bottom heat. Then put in the refrigerator for about 20 minutes (to cut it better).

node.text:
Hublot first released the Big Bang in 2005. Since then, this model has come to embody Swiss watchmaking in the third millennium.
In 2018, the first connected version of the Big Bang made its debut. And now, Hublot unveils the #BigBangE. The new incarnation of the brand's Art of Fusion ethos: a fusion between tradition and innovation, cutting edge materials and the latest digital technology.
For the first time in Hublot's history, this watch will be sold online on our website. It will then be available to purchase in boutiques and the traditional network. Stay tuned!
Discover more on https://www.hublot.com/watches/big-bang/big-bang-e-black-ceramic-42-mm

node.text:
Hublot has made the impossible possible by transmuting gold into its rarest and most exclusive form: gold crystal. This form of gold is unique, since it is impossible to reproduce two identical gold crystals. 

Beyond the fascination that gold has exerted on man since the dawn of time, it embodies everything that makes Hublot so distinctive: materials, minerals, metals; their fusion and their transformation into new forms of expression, unique and quite unexpected. An alchemy expressed both in the transmutation of the raw material and in the chemistry created by the spirit of the watch itself. This is the new #SpiritOfBigBang #GoldCrystal, available in a 42mm or 39mm case.

node.text: Discover the new #BigBangDJSnake, with an iridescent shine, and countless blue and purple hues. The bezel of this exclusive timepiece is treated with a special and technical manufacturing process, similar to a black PVD treatment. During the process, the different components of the watch must each be placed in specific positions when they are coated with different colors. The result is an optical effect in which the colors of the watch change depending on the light and when viewed from different angles. @djsnake #DJSnake
